<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cce6825f55ba05353e3652d8989b6137?s=50"></div><header><strong>swift-package-manager support in CocoaPods</strong> from <string>Will Entriken</string> &lt;fulldecent at gmail.com&gt;<p>April 15, 2016 at 11:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>Hello,<br></p><p>I am working with the CocoaPods project, which is a way to publish and get<br>exposure for Swift libraries.<br></p><p>Specifically I am working on the pod-template project which is the<br>recommended and supported way for all new library authors to model their<br>projects.<br></p><p>I hope that we can update this template to be simultaneously compatible<br>with Swift Package Manager so that libraries created using the pod-template<br>recommendations will immediately be available to Swift Package Manager<br>consumers.<br></p><p>For a lower bound on the installed base of pod-template users, please<br>search GitHub for this default text from pod-template.<br></p><p>&gt; &quot;To run the example project, clone the repo, and run&quot;<br></p><p>If anyone would please be able to assist with this, please follow this<br>issue at a minimum and help provide guidance in test casing and<br>implementing this goal.<br></p><p>&gt; https://github.com/CocoaPods/pod-template/issues/157<br></p><p>Thank you,<br></p><p>Will<br></p><p><br>William Entriken<br>267-738-4201<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-users/attachments/20160415/55721662/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></div>    </main>
